<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strncpy(_metal.page_sizes[index].path, path, PATH_MAX) can read up to PATH_MAX bytes from the source 'path' without checking that 'path' is a NUL-terminated string at or before PATH_MAX. If a caller passes a pointer to a char object that is smaller than PATH_MAX (or not NUL-terminated within its bounds), strncpy may read beyond the bounds of that source object, causing an out-of-bounds access. (Additionally, if the source length >= PATH_MAX the destination will not be NUL-terminated, which can lead to later out-of-bounds reads.)
</scenario>

